{#
  /sanctions/sector/<slug> — A–Z directory of every OFAC SDN
  designation classified into one sector (military / economic /
  diplomatic / governance).

  Sister page to /sanctions/<bucket> — same A–Z UX, but pivoted on
  sector instead of entity-type. The H1 deliberately uses the word
  "currently" to match the GSC query that motivated this page
  ("ofac sdn list current military, economic, diplomatic"); freshness
  copy reinforces it.

  Each name links to the same /sanctions/<bucket>/<slug> profile that
  the bucket-based index links to — one profile, two paths in.
#}
{% extends "_base.html.j2" %}
{% from "_cluster_nav.html.j2" import cluster_nav %}

{% block content %}
<div class="container-wide">
  <nav class="breadcrumbs" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
    <a href="/">Home</a>
    <span>›</span>
    <a href="/sanctions-tracker">OFAC Cuba Sanctions</a>
    <span>›</span>
    <a href="/sanctions/by-sector">By sector</a>
    <span>›</span>
    <strong>{{ sector_label }}</strong>
  </nav>

  <article>
    <header>
      <div style="font-size:12px; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:1.4px; color:var(--sr-red); font-weight:700;">
        Live tracker · {{ today_human }} · {{ profiles|length }} active designations
      </div>
      <h1>OFAC Cuba SDN — Currently Sanctioned {{ sector_label }} ({{ profiles|length }})</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">
        Every {{ sector_label|lower }} on the US Treasury OFAC SDN List under
        Cuba-related sanctions programs. Each name links to a permanent
        profile with biographical data, OFAC program code, and source link.
      </p>
      <div class="meta">
        <span><strong>Source:</strong> US Treasury OFAC SDN List</span>
        <span><strong>Refreshed:</strong> twice daily (10am &amp; 5pm ET)</span>
        <span><strong>Programs covered:</strong> CUBA (CACR, 31 CFR Part 515), Cuba Restricted List (State Dept), Helms-Burton</span>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="body">
      <div class="takeaways">
        <h3>What "{{ sector_label|lower }}" means here</h3>
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 14px;">{{ sector_description }}</p>
      </div>

      <p>
        Switch between sector views:
      </p>
      <ul>
        {% for s in sectors_nav %}
        <li>
          {% if s.key == active_key %}
          <strong>{{ s.label }} ({{ s.count }})</strong> — current view
          {% else %}
          <a href="{{ s.url_path }}"><strong>{{ s.label }}</strong></a> ({{ s.count }})
          {% endif %}
        </li>
        {% endfor %}
      </ul>

      <h2>All {{ sector_label|lower }} (A–Z)</h2>
      {% if grouped %}
      {% for letter, items in grouped %}
      <h3 id="{{ letter }}">{{ letter }}</h3>
      <ul class="related">
        {% for p in items %}
        <li>
          <a href="{{ p.url_path }}">{{ p.display_name }}</a>
          <small>— {{ p.program or 'CUBA' }} ·
            {{ p.category_singular }}{% if p.parsed.dob %} · DOB {{ p.parsed.dob }}{% elif p.parsed.imo %} · IMO {{ p.parsed.imo }}{% elif p.parsed.aircraft_tail %} · Tail {{ p.parsed.aircraft_tail }}{% endif %}</small>
        </li>
        {% endfor %}
      </ul>
      {% endfor %}
      {% else %}
      <p>No designations are currently classified under this sector.</p>
      {% endif %}

      <h2>Why this view exists</h2>
      <p>
        OFAC publishes the Cuba SDN list grouped only by entity type
        (individuals / entities / vessels / aircraft) and by sanctions program.
        Compliance, M&amp;A, and journalist research workflows usually want a
        sector-pivoted view — "who are the currently-sanctioned FAR/MININT
        officials?" or "which GAESA-affiliated entities are blocked?" — which
        neither OFAC nor most trackers offer. We compute the sector for every
        designation from its OFAC remarks plus a curated overrides table; see
        the <a href="/sanctions/by-sector">sector pillar page</a> for the full
        methodology.
      </p>

      <h2>Verifying these designations</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://sanctions-search.ofac.treasury.gov/" rel="nofollow">OFAC official Sanctions Search</a> — primary source for live screening</li>
        <li><a href="/tools/ofac-cuba-sanctions-checker">Our search tool</a> — paste any name to see if it's currently designated</li>
        <li><a href="/tools/ofac-cuba-general-licenses">Active OFAC General Licenses for Cuba (CACR §515.560–.578)</a></li>
        <li><a href="/explainers/what-are-ofac-sanctions-on-cuba">What are OFAC sanctions on Cuba? (plain-English guide)</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </article>

  {% from "_notify_cta.html.j2" import notify_cta %}
  {{ notify_cta(
      heading="Get alerted when Cuba sanctions change",
      subtext="SDN additions, removals, and sector-level program changes — delivered the same day OFAC publishes them.",
      tag="sanctions-changes",
      notes="Signed up from sanctions by-sector page"
  ) }}

  {{ cluster_nav(cluster_ctx) }}
</div>
{% endblock %}
